content.description: Start on two edges. Climb left through awesome sloper rail features to an easing top. The detached ramp is off.
content.protection: 2-3 Pads. The landing is better than it first appears.
content.location: From the pullout, follow the cliff band to the right (SE) for about 5 mins. This boulder is past the Daylily boulder.

content.description: Start matched in the crack on a triangle block.
content.location: 25 yards left of Daylily on an elevated rocky platform. Great little landing pad, but a fall off the platform would not be nice.

content.description: Sit start with right hand edge and left hand side pull. Climb tricky moves up the slab.
content.location: ~1 min past Wood Violet

content.description: Start on side pulls and climb the vertical features.
content.location: From the roadside pullout, hike ~2-5 mins left (NW). This boulder is just to the left of the Prototaxites project.

content.description: Stand start on side pulls. Climb the short bulge.
content.location: Uphill and around the corner of Lion's Mane, along the social trail.

content.description: Start on the large ledge. A delicate mantle leads to the lower angle slab, where cool holds and desperate moves await.
content.location: To the right of Prototaxites, on the same boulder. Follow the cliffband NW from the pullout for ~1-2 min and you will see these looming slabs from below.

content.description: Climb the cool compression feature to a tricky topout (for the grade). A classic warmup!
content.location: From the roadside pullout, hike 5-10 mins left (NW). This boulder is just past chanterelle (on the same outcrop) and just before Garden Variety.

content.description: Short but sweet route starts with obvious left hand side pull. Find a few more holds and then bust a big move to a good hold.. top out on juggy ledges.    Movement on here is good and the holds are all positive. V2 for shorter folks
content.location: Just left of the slab climb Daylily. Walk right along the cliffband towards Wood Violet

content.description: SDS on left hand side pull and right hand crimp. Climb through the thin seam to a sweet sloper pinch and a huge dyno.
content.location: About 10 steps from the car on the first gently overhanging face by the roadside pullout.

content.description: Stand start on sloper jug. Climb sidepulls up gently overhanging wall. Detached blocks and wall to the right are not used.
content.location: To the right of Shiitake, on the same wall. Easily seen from the roadside pullout.

content.description: Sit start with left hand on rounded arete and right hand sloper. Several slaps lead over the bulge. Pretty fun, for a dumpy boulder.
content.location: Uphill and around the corner of Lion's Mane, along the social trail

content.description: Start the same as Garden Variety (matched in the thin crack) and do the first move, but instead of jumping to the lip, continue following the crack left.
content.location: From the parking head left and work your way down the cliff band for a few minutes.  This climb is just past the boulders Chanterelle and Spore, on a short, steep wall with an obvious thin crack.

content.description: An intriguing move that might just suck you in..  and with the pretty cool grips.  Start left hand on the arete on the best spot (about head height) and right on a low prominent sidepull.  Fire to the lip and move left to finish.
content.protection: A few pads.  Landing does slant and you just might swing out.
content.location: Left side of Garden Variety Boulder.  Boulder just right of Death Cap Boulder.

content.description: Start in the break, with good feet. Climb directly up the blank slab to the right of the crack seam.
content.location: From the roadside pullout, follow the cliff band left (NW) for 2-5 mins. This looming slab will be visible from below.

content.description: Stand start with left hand on arete and right hand with good edge on the face. Climb tenuous moves up the sloper arete and rail systems. Detached blocks are not used.
content.location: Follow the cliffband about 2-5 mins left (NW) of the roadside pullout. This climb is just past the Prototaxites Project.

content.description: Sit start matched on good edge. Climb cool features up the slab.
content.location: Left side of the roadside pullout cliff band. Just before Lion's Mane.

content.description: Start on two positive vertical edges. Climb the slab.
content.location: Around the corner of Morel Compass, on the same boulder.

content.description: SDS on arete with left hand edge and right hand gaston. Climb the arete up and left, eventually topping out as for Deathcap.
content.location: To the right of Deathcap, on the same boulder.

content.description: Start on good edges. Long moves lead up the slab.
content.location: On the left side of the Roadside pullout cliff band. Just to the left of Mycelium

content.description: Stand start on large sidepull jug. Climb cool rounded granite rails up the slab.
content.location: To the right of daylily, on the same boulder.

content.description: Top side pull tricky switch grip
content.location: Just left of goombas above puffball

content.description: SDS on sidepull rail. Climb straight up through crack systems to a tricky top.
content.location: Just above and slightly left of Nystatin.

content.description: Start lower rock move up the arete to reaching top out
content.location: Just above puffball Boulder

content.description: Start matched in the thin crack. Bust a big move left and proceed to negotiate the tricky lip mantle.
content.location: From the roadside pullout, hike 5-10 mins left (NW). This boulder is just before the Deathcap/Morel Compass boulder and is hard to miss.

content.description: Climb obvious features to top.
content.location: Immediately right of Lion's Mane.

content.description: Start on the jug at chest height. Climb straight up through good holds and interesting moves.
content.location: From the roadside pullout, follow the cliff band to the left (NW) for about 5-10 mins. It's a little further down than you might expect.

content.description: Start on left hand side pull and right hand flat edge. Climb the tall slab. Stays on you the whole time.
content.location: From the roadside pullout, follow the cliff band to the right (SE) for 2-5 mins. This slab is pretty easily spotted.

content.description: Start as for "Puffball" (left hand on arete, right hand on low sidepull edge on left side of the wall). After sticking the first move of that, traverse the slopey lip to the mantle of "Backyard Forager" on the far right side of the wall.
content.location: Garden Variety boulder. Left of the pullout by about 10 mins

content.description: Sit start on jug break. Climb the striking arete.
content.location: From the roadside pullout, hike 5-10 mins left (NW). This boulder pops into view after a short break in the cliff band.

content.description: Starting left hand on arete and right low on undercling/sidepull, move up prow to tricky top out.
content.location: Just left of 1-Up and Ascomycota.

content.description: Sit start in the dihedral left of Death Cap with a jug left hand undercling and right hand on a small dihedral edge above the jug. Climb up the dihedral with tricky feet
content.location: Left of Deathcap

content.description: Starts as for Wood Violet, but climbs straight up using crack and cool holds. The detached ramp is off.
content.location: To the right of Wood Violet

content.description: Start on two edges in the horizontal rail. Do a long pull, then mantle the lip.
content.location: To the right of Garden Variety, on the same boulder

content.description: Squeeze the mushroomy prow. Sit start with right hand incut slopey hold and left hand perfect half pad crimp. Thruch out left and start compressing.
content.location: 50 feet to the right of Chanterelle.

content.description: Starts on obvious lower right jug with a high left foot and climbs through the diagonal seam up and left to top out.
content.location: 70ish yards down and right of Chanterelle. Closest boulder to the road as the escarpment takes a sharp bend.

content.description: Stand start matched on a sloper. Follow sloper rail to the right, eventually reaching a tricky topout mantle.
content.protection: Pads. The landing is tiered, which makes it hard to protect
content.location: To the right of Nystatin, which is just past the large Prototaxites slab.

content.description: Start right hand undercling, left slope.. Move right via a long reach and likely a dyno, depending on reach, into the center of the face and top out.  On boulder right of Baby Bella and same boulder (and finish) as Ascomycota.
The largest and most developed outcropping at Chute Pond. This area hosts stellar problems in all grade ranges. The first boulders are steps from the car!
